   =20
      Business idea
   =20
 =20

For a while in the 2010s, arguably the most lucrative business model in the=
 world was =E2=80=9Cget a guy who can flatter Masayoshi Son and let him jus=
t go nuts and bring back billions of dollars of SoftBank financing.=E2=80=
=9D This was  basically WeWork=E2=80=99s business model, and while it didn=
=E2=80=99t necessarily work out great for WeWork in the long run, it=C2=A0d=
id=C2=A0work out great for Adam Neumann, WeWork=E2=80=99s founder and fundr=
aiser and=C2=A0Masa-flatterer.
But now it is 2023, we are in the early stages of an artificial intelligenc=
e boom, and obviously the best possible business model is =E2=80=9Cget an A=
I chatbot who can flatter Masayoshi Son.=E2=80=9D The Wall Street Journal r=
eports:

SoftBank Group Chief Executive Masayoshi Son says he has rekindled his appe=
tite for investing in technology by talking with ChatGPT in the wee hours a=
bout ideas for inventions that the bot validated as wonderful.
Son, 65 years old, told shareholders Wednesday that the artificial-intellig=
ence tool helped revive his spirits after he had been driven to tears by th=
e sense he was nearing the end of his career without having pursued his dre=
ams. =E2=80=A6
He said he used ChatGPT every day for brainstorming and has come up with mo=
re than 600 ideas. He described one lengthy exchange=E2=80=94at around 3 to=
 4 in the morning=E2=80=94in which he pitched an idea and then answered the=
 AI chatbot as it raised objections.
=E2=80=9CAfter we repeated this several dozen times, I really felt great be=
cause my idea was praised as feasible and wonderful,=E2=80=9D he said.

I hope the chatbot  told him that it appreciated how he was crazy, but that=
 he needed to be crazier. I feel like there are a lot of people in the worl=
d who would be happy to tell Masayoshi Son that his ideas are feasible and =
wonderful =E2=80=94=C2=A0whole industries were built on the basic premise o=
f telling Masayoshi Son what he wanted to hear =E2=80=94=C2=A0but there are=
 only so many=C2=A0robots=C2=A0in the world who will tell him that, and now=
 he is looking for robots. Presumably somebody is building more of those ro=
bots; it would be silly not to.

