ank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; ba=
ckground-color: #ccc;"> talked about its proposal last year</a>. I thought =
it was cool! Traditional finance involves a lot of <em>unsecured=C2=A0credi=
t risk</em>, while crypto was building a system that was much more based on=
 <em>real-time collateral</em>; Bankman-Fried argued, rather compellingly, =
that the crypto approach might be <em>safer</em>.</li>=09<li style=3D"margi=
n-bottom: 5px;">We have <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/=
click/31860043.264406/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljb=
GVzLzIwMjItMDEtMTkvd2FzaGluZy13ZWIzP2NtcGlkPUJCRDA2MjEyM19NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0=
