k" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom=
-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; back=
ground-color: #ccc;"> turned out</a> to just give all of FTX=E2=80=99s cust=
omer money to its affiliated trading firm.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-botto=
m: 5px;">The problem with tokenomics is that the US Securities and Exchange=
 Commission thinks, correctly, that all of these tokens that convey a finan=
cial stake in the system <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com=
/click/31860043.264406/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGlj=
bGVzLzIwMjMtMDYtMDcvd2hlbi1pcy1hLXRva2VuLW5vdC1hLXNlY3VyaXR5P2NtcGlkPUJCRDA=
2MjEyM19NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJn=
V0bV90ZXJtPTIzMDYyMSZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a2=
3cB33fa0a20" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blan=
k" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom=
-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; back=
ground-color: #ccc;">  are <em>securities</em></a>, and so have to be regis=
tered with the SEC, which is very hard for crypto platforms to do. All of t=
hese tokens seem to be illegal, or at least legally very dicey, in the US.<=
/li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Everyone stopped talking about blo=
ckchain, and stock exchanges that excitedly announced their blockchain plan=
s in 2017 have <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/318=
